This paper deals with designing algorithms for computing approximately revenue-maximizing sequential posted-pricing mechanisms in multi-unit auctions, which is a problem in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithms involve efficient computation and approximation techniques, which are common in computer science theory (cs.DS). The problem also involves Bayesian information and decision-making, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The goal of maximizing revenue is a central problem in economics and mechanism design (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses approximation algorithms and polynomial time algorithms, which are topics in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
